        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 2:48PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Camp Verde to near Bandera to near Mico.
Movement was west at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Medina, Hondo, Bandera, Vanderpool, Tarpley, D'Hanis, New Fountain,
Quihi, Mico, Utopia, Hill Country State Natural Area, Lost Maples
State Natural Area, Lakehills, and Lake Medina Shores.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
